              <h2>How Virginia income tax works</h2>
              <p>
                Virginia uses a simple four-bracket progressive income tax
                system. Unlike some states, the top rate of
                <strong>5.75%</strong> kicks in at relatively low income levels,
                so most middle‑ and high‑income residents pay that top marginal
                rate on at least part of their income.
              </p>

