              <h2>Frequently asked questions about Virginia income tax</h2>

              <h3>Do Virginia counties or cities charge extra income tax?</h3>
              <p>
                No. Virginia does <strong>not</strong> have local income taxes
                like some other states. However, many localities levy separate
                taxes such as personal property tax on vehicles, local sales
                tax, and various fees. Those are <strong>not</strong> included
                in this calculator.
              </p>

              <h3>Is my Social Security income taxed in Virginia?</h3>
              <p>
                Virginia generally follows federal rules for Social Security. If
                your benefits are not taxable on your federal return, they are
                usually not taxable in Virginia. If part of your benefits are
                taxable federally, that amount flows into your Virginia AGI and
                may be taxed, subject to Virginia‑specific subtractions and
                age‑based deductions.
              </p>

              <h3>When are Virginia income tax returns due?</h3>
              <p>
                Virginia individual income tax returns are typically due on
                <strong>May 1</strong> following the end of the tax year, though
                deadlines can shift slightly if they fall on weekends or
                holidays. Extensions to file may be available, but they do not
                extend the time to pay any tax due.
              </p>

              <h3>
                Where can I find official Virginia tax forms and instructions?
              </h3>
              <p>
                The official source is the
                <a
                  href="https://www.tax.virginia.gov/"
